    <item>
      <title>Creating This Website</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/tinker/2025-06-03/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 03 Jun 2025 17:36:22 -0500</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/tinker/2025-06-03/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;It&amp;rsquo;s been almost 7 years since I&amp;rsquo;ve created this website, and it&amp;rsquo;s time for an upgrade.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This is what it used to look like: &lt;a href=&#34;http://2018.www.marcuschiu.com/&#34;&gt;http://2018.www.marcuschiu.com/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;It has nice bouncy animations, but I want more:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;I need a way to write about my journey for each project. Which I could with the old website, however it&amp;rsquo;s just not builtin to the website. It&amp;rsquo;s just pure HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;I also need a way to embed different domains of my life in a single place. Such as art, music, and the occasional rambles.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;For the past 6 months, I&amp;rsquo;ve used WordPress to store my rambles (i.e. &lt;a href=&#34;http://thoughts.marcuschiu.com&#34;&gt;thoughts.marcuschiu.com&lt;/a&gt;). I could use it as my main site and add a tab for &lt;em&gt;tinkerings&lt;/em&gt; and what not - buuuuuuuut NO. I want something else :)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
